Market Analysis and Insights :

Global Foodservice Equipment Market

The foodservice equipment market is expected to witness market growth at a rate of 5% in the forecast period of 2021 to 2028, and will reach the value of USD 49,422.65 million by 2028. Data Bridge Market Research report on foodservice equipment market provides analysis and insights regarding the various factors expected to be prevalent throughout the forecast period while providing their impacts on the marketâ€™s growth. The rise in the food and beverage globally is escalating the growth of foodservice equipment market.

Food service equipment refer to the type of equipment that are utilized for preparation and storage of food products for commercial purposes. The equipment consists of storage & handling equipment, food & beverage preparation equipment, cooking equipment, serving equipment and ware washing equipment. They are used in the food service industry such as hotels, and restaurants, among other commercial kitchens.

The continuous development of the hospitality industry across the globe acts as one of the major factors driving the growth of foodservice equipment market. The rise in demand for multi-functional, efficient, space & time saving, and reduced labor, and enhanced demand for takeaways accelerate the market growth. The use of these equipment for preparing and storing food, such as ranges, cooking stoves, and electrical refrigerators, to the availability of custom food service appliances to cook different cuisines, and availability of wide range of technologically-advanced and innovative products further influence the market. Additionally, urbanization and digitization, expansion of food and beverage sector and increase in number of hotels and restaurants, positively affect the foodservice equipment market. Furthermore, rapid technological advancements extend profitable opportunities to the market players in the forecast period of 2021 to 2028.

On the other hand, high capital investment and complexities associated with the usage of these equipment are expected to obstruct the market growth. The negative impact of COVID-19 on the hospitality industry is projected to challenge the foodservice equipment market in the forecast period of 2021-2028.

